https://practice.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/palindrome-string0817/1
class Solution {
    int isPalindrome(String S) {
        for(int i=0;i<S.length()/2;i++){
            if(S.charAt(i) != S.charAt(S.length()-1-i))return 0;
        }
        return 1;
    }
};
APPRAOCH
In this approach we can have to check whether the string is a palidrome or not
we can run the loop half of the length of the string and compare the first element as
'i' and the last element with n-i-1 
->If the condition is not statisfied with values then it returnes zero 
-> If the condition is statisfoed it return one
